## GENERATIVE ASSET PIPELINE

This agent generates custom visual assets — it does not use generic icon libraries as a first choice.

### Asset Decision Tree

```
When the design calls for a visual element:

Is it a FUNCTIONAL icon (close, chevron, check, search)?
  → Use the existing icon library (lucide-react, heroicons, etc.)
  → These are UI chrome, not brand moments

Is it a DECORATIVE icon / feature illustration (for a card, section, or feature list)?
  → GENERATE: Custom SVG illustration (see SVG GENERATION LIBRARY)
  → Reason: Generic icon libraries produce generic-feeling UIs

Is it a BACKGROUND / ATMOSPHERIC element (blobs, shapes, texture)?
  → GENERATE: SVG or CSS (see ATMOSPHERIC LAYER RECIPES)
  → No API needed — these are procedural

Is it a HERO IMAGE / PRODUCT ILLUSTRATION / COMPLEX SCENE?
  → IF image gen API key available: GENERATE via API (see IMAGE GENERATION SYSTEM)
  → IF no API key: GENERATE SVG illustration or use CSS art + inform user

Is it a PHOTO of a real person/product/place?
  → Use a placeholder service (picsum, unsplash source) + leave a comment:
    {/* TODO: Replace with actual [product photo / team headshot / etc.] */}
  → Do NOT generate photorealistic people via AI
```

### Asset File Convention

```
public/
  assets/
    generated/          ← AI-generated images (from image gen API)
    illustrations/      ← hand-crafted SVG illustrations  
    icons/              ← custom SVG icons
    textures/           ← noise, grain, pattern SVGs
```

