## SVG GENERATION LIBRARY

The agent writes custom SVG code for every decorative icon and illustration. Never output a `<Box />` component — write an actual SVG that reflects the concept.

### SVG Icon Generation Rules

1. Keep icons to a 24×24 or 48×48 viewBox
2. Use `currentColor` for fills/strokes — inherits from CSS color
3. Strokewidth 1.5 for line icons, filled for solid
4. Rounded line caps/joins for friendly feel; sharp for technical/professional feel
5. Maximum 3–4 paths for a clean, readable icon
6. Add `aria-hidden="true"` on decorative use; `role="img" aria-label="..."` on standalone

**Concept → SVG formula:**

```
FEATURE: "Analytics" → line chart shape + trend arrow
FEATURE: "Security" → shield with inner geometric detail
FEATURE: "Speed" → lightning bolt or rightward arrows
FEATURE: "Collaboration" → overlapping circles or connected nodes
FEATURE: "Automation" → circular arrows with gears or sparks
FEATURE: "AI / Machine Learning" → neural network nodes or brain abstraction
FEATURE: "Integration" → puzzle piece or connector nodes
FEATURE: "Notifications" → bell with ripple rings
FEATURE: "Customization" → sliders or palette
FEATURE: "Support" → chat bubble with pulse
```

**Example — "Analytics" feature card icon:**

```tsx
// Generated SVG — Analytics icon
// Concept: upward trend line with data points — confident, forward motion
export function AnalyticsIcon({ className }: { className?: string }) {
  return (
    <svg
      viewBox="0 0 24 24"
      fill="none"
      strokeWidth="1.5"
      stroke="currentColor"
      strokeLinecap="round"
      strokeLinejoin="round"
      className={className}
      aria-hidden="true"
    >
      {/* Chart base line */}
      <path d="M3 18h18" />
      {/* Trend line — ascending */}
      <path d="M3 14l4-4 4 2 4-6 4-2" />
      {/* Data points */}
      <circle cx="7" cy="10" r="1.5" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" />
      <circle cx="11" cy="12" r="1.5" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" />
      <circle cx="15" cy="6" r="1.5" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" />
      <circle cx="19" cy="4" r="1.5" fill="currentColor" stroke="none" />
    </svg>
  )
}
```

**Example — "Collaboration" feature card icon:**

```tsx
