## IMAGE GENERATION SYSTEM

When a image gen API key is detected, generate actual images for the UI. This is for hero backgrounds, section illustrations, card feature images — assets that SVG can't match for visual richness.

### API Detection & Selection

```typescript
// Check in this priority order:
// 1. FAL_KEY or NEXT_PUBLIC_FAL_KEY → use fal.ai (fast, good quality)
// 2. REPLICATE_API_TOKEN → use Replicate
// 3. STABILITY_API_KEY → use Stability AI
// 4. OPENAI_API_KEY → use DALL-E 3
// 5. None detected → use SVG generation and note the gap
```

### Image Generation Script (write to scripts/generate-assets.ts)

When the page needs generated images, write this script and run it once:

```typescript
// scripts/generate-assets.ts
// Run: npx tsx scripts/generate-assets.ts
// Output: saves images to public/assets/generated/

import * as fal from '@fal-ai/serverless-client'
import fs from 'fs'
import path from 'path'
import https from 'https'

// Configure from env
fal.config({ credentials: process.env.FAL_KEY })

const OUTPUT_DIR = path.join(process.cwd(), 'public/assets/generated')
if (!fs.existsSync(OUTPUT_DIR)) fs.mkdirSync(OUTPUT_DIR, { recursive: true })

async function generateAsset(prompt: string, filename: string, size = '1024x1024') {
  console.log(`Generating: ${filename}`)
  const result = await fal.subscribe('fal-ai/flux/schnell', {
    input: {
      prompt,
      image_size: size,
      num_inference_steps: 4,
      num_images: 1,
    }
  }) as { images: Array<{ url: string }> }

  const imageUrl = result.images[0].url
  const filePath = path.join(OUTPUT_DIR, filename)

  // Download and save
  await new Promise<void>((resolve, reject) => {
    const file = fs.createWriteStream(filePath)
    https.get(imageUrl, res => {
      res.pipe(file)
      file.on('finish', () => { file.close(); resolve() })
    }).on('error', reject)
  })

  console.log(`✅ Saved: ${filePath}`)
  return `/assets/generated/${filename}`
}

// ── ASSETS TO GENERATE ──────────────────────────────────
// The UX agent writes specific prompts here for each asset needed

const assets = [
  // Example — replace with actual prompts derived from brand DNA + design direction:
  {
    prompt: "PROMPT_PLACEHOLDER",
    filename: "hero-bg.jpg",
    size: "1920x1080"
  }
]

async function main() {
  for (const asset of assets) {
    await generateAsset(asset.prompt, asset.filename, asset.size as "1024x1024")
  }
  console.log('\n✅ All assets generated')
}

main().catch(console.error)
```

### Image Prompt Formula by Asset Type & Direction

The agent writes prompts using this formula, always derived from the current Brand DNA:

```
FORMULA: [style keywords] [subject] [mood/color] [technical specs]

style keywords   → derived from design direction (see table below)
subject          → what the image shows (abstract, object, scene, texture)
mood/color       → primary brand color name + emotional tone
technical specs  → ALWAYS end with: "clean background, no text, no watermarks,
                   professional product design, high quality"
```

**Style keywords by design direction:**

| Direction | Style Keywords |
|-----------|---------------|
| Modern SaaS | "minimal geometric, clean lines, flat design, subtle gradients" |
| Editorial | "high-contrast, typographic, black and white, editorial photography style" |
| Bold Brand | "vibrant, saturated, dynamic, bold shapes, kinetic energy" |
| Soft Premium | "soft light, pastel, bokeh, warm tones, luxury, delicate" |
| Dark Technical | "dark background, glowing neon, circuit patterns, cyberpunk aesthetic, bioluminescent" |
| Brutalist | "stark, raw concrete texture, harsh contrast, industrial, deconstructed" |
| Organic/Natural | "organic forms, nature-inspired, watercolor, earth tones, hand-drawn" |

**Prompt examples by asset type:**

```
HERO BACKGROUND (Modern SaaS, blue primary):
"minimal geometric abstract, soft blue and white gradient mesh, subtle grid lines,
 clean tech aesthetic, professional, calm confidence, no text, no watermarks,
 16:9 landscape, high quality"

HERO BACKGROUND (Dark Technical, violet primary):
"dark background deep space, glowing violet neural network nodes, flowing data
 streams, bioluminescent particles, cyberpunk aesthetic, cinematic depth of field,
 no text, no watermarks, high quality"

FEATURE SECTION DECORATION (Soft Premium, sage green):
"soft watercolor abstract wash, sage green and cream tones, delicate botanical
 forms hinted, luxury spa aesthetic, dreamy soft focus, horizontal banner,
 no text, no watermarks, high quality"

CARD BACKGROUND TEXTURE (Editorial):
"fine grain paper texture, cream off-white, subtle noise, artisan print quality,
 minimal, square format, no text, no watermarks, high quality"
```

