## BLEND MODE & COMPOSITING LIBRARY

CSS blend modes are what make generated images feel *integrated* into the design, not pasted in.

### Blend Mode Reference

```css
/* Image blends INTO the background color */
.blend-multiply  { mix-blend-mode: multiply; }   /* dark areas darken bg — good for light bg */
.blend-screen    { mix-blend-mode: screen; }      /* light areas lighten bg — good for dark bg */
.blend-overlay   { mix-blend-mode: overlay; }     /* increases contrast — punchy effect */
.blend-soft-light{ mix-blend-mode: soft-light; }  /* subtle contrast/saturation boost */
.blend-color     { mix-blend-mode: color; }       /* applies image hue to bg lightness */
.blend-luminosity{ mix-blend-mode: luminosity; }  /* applies bg hue to image lightness */
```

**Use case matrix:**

| Asset type | Background | Best blend mode | Effect |
|-----------|-----------|-----------------|--------|
| Noise texture overlay | Any light bg | `multiply` | Texture darkens naturally |
| Noise texture overlay | Any dark bg | `screen` | Texture lightens naturally |
| Atmospheric color blob | White bg | `multiply` | Color washes into page |
| Atmospheric color blob | Dark bg | `screen` | Color glows into page |
| Generated texture | Card surface | `soft-light` | Subtle depth without color shift |
| Duotone image | Brand primary | `color` | Full brand color toning |

**Duotone recipe (makes any image feel on-brand):**

```css
/* Makes any photo feel branded — two-color treatment */
.duotone-primary {
  filter: grayscale(1) contrast(1.1);
}
.duotone-primary::after {
  content: '';
  position: absolute;
  inset: 0;
  background: linear-gradient(
    135deg,
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--primary) 60%, transparent),
    color-mix(in srgb, var(--accent) 40%, transparent)
  );
  mix-blend-mode: color;
}
```

### CSS Mask Recipes (for soft-edge integration)

```css
/* Fade image into background — bottom edge */
.fade-bottom {
  -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, black 60%, transparent 100%);
  mask-image: linear-gradient(to bottom, black 60%, transparent 100%);
}

/* Fade image into background — right edge (for split layouts) */
.fade-right {
  -webkit-mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, black 50%, transparent 100%);
  mask-image: linear-gradient(to right, black 50%, transparent 100%);
}

/* Vignette (dark edges, bright center) */
.vignette {
  -webkit-mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 80% at center, black 60%, transparent 100%);
  mask-image: radial-gradient(ellipse 80% 80% at center, black 60%, transparent 100%);
}

/* Spotlight (bright center only) */
.spotlight {
  -webkit-mask-image: radial-gradient(circle 300px at var(--x, 50%) var(--y, 50%), black, transparent);
  mask-image: radial-gradient(circle 300px at var(--x, 50%) var(--y, 50%), black, transparent);
