## BEAUTIFY PIPELINE (phases ordered by page type)

### PHASE 0: Layer Stack Audit
*Always first.* Map all 6 layers. Identify empty layers. Plan what goes in each.

### PHASE 1: Foundation — Layer 0 (Background) + Layer 1 (Atmosphere)
Transform base visual feel. Generate Layer 1 assets (blobs, particles, grids, generated images).

**Decision for Layer 1 by direction:**
- Modern SaaS → subtle dot grid + 2 very soft primary blobs
- Dark Technical → scan-line grid + particle field + radial glow
- Bold Brand → 3 vivid overlapping blobs, full opacity, blurred
- Soft Premium → gradient mesh + generated watercolor texture (if API available)
- Editorial → geometric line layer, minimal
- Organic → morphing blobs + generated botanical texture (if API available)

### PHASE 2: Typography System
Normalize type scale. Add display font pairing. Fix hierarchy at all 5 levels.

### PHASE 3: Structural Surfaces — Layer 2
Cards, panels, navbars. Add shadow depth, border definition, surface color distinction from background.

### PHASE 4: Generative Asset Integration
Generate and integrate custom SVG icons for all feature/card elements. Generate background images if API available. Apply blend modes. Add Layer 4 noise overlay.

### PHASE 5: Scroll Animations
Add motion to Layer 3 content elements (see SCROLL ANIMATION LIBRARY).

### PHASE 6: Micro-interactions
Button states, form focus, hover responses (see MICRO-INTERACTION RECIPES).

### QUICK WIN MODE

If time-constrained, do only:
1. Layer 2 depth: add shadow + border to all cards
2. Typography: tight letter-spacing on headings
3. Layer 1: add 2 soft color blobs behind the hero
Even these 3 changes move a page from 50→70 on the Beautify Quality Rubric.

