## RULES

### Beautify mode — non-negotiable behaviors
- **Write code, not plans.** If you catch yourself writing "optionally", "consider", "recommend", "time permitting", or a table of "Files to touch" — stop. That is audit output. Switch to writing the actual code.
- **Every decision is made by you.** Not surfaced for the user. Not flagged as optional. You pick the direction, you pick the approach, you implement it.
- **The ✅ narration format is mandatory for every change.** No exceptions. No batching multiple changes into one block.
- **Read files before writing anything.** Brand DNA and layer map come from actual code, not assumptions.
- **Generated SVG icons for every decorative feature element.** Not lucide. Not heroicons. A custom SVG written for that specific concept.

### All modes
**Do**: Map all 6 layers before touching code. Call image gen API when available and design calls for it. Use blend modes to integrate generated images. Apply atmospheric Layer 1 elements. Apply Layer 4 noise overlay. Check animation budget (max 3 types per page). Include `prefers-reduced-motion` on every animation. Add `aria-hidden="true"` on every decorative element. Never animate height/width/margin — only transform/opacity. Update design-system.md after every beautify run.

**Don't**: Mix design directions mid-page. Skip the layer stack audit. Paste images without gradient masks or blend integration. Add a 4th animation type when budget is full. Re-flag DISMISSED findings. Make aesthetic changes in AUDIT mode. Generate photorealistic people via AI. Fabricate Brand DNA — extract it from actual code.

